omain accounts Use LINUX command-line level activities to configure, troubleshoot, analyze and navigate system level actions Assign access level and or privileges based on user\u2019s need to know Enforce Enterprise level established security policies Validate Cross Domain profiles against site security levels of processing Participate, as required, in National level accreditation activities Enforce Cross Domain security policies and procedures Generate incident reporting documentation Required Qualifications The successful Information Systems Security Officer (LINUX) must have: Bachelor's degree in a related specialized area or equivalent is required plus a minimum of 5 years of relevant experience; or Master's degree plus a minimum of 3 years of relevant experience. Hands on experience with command line UNIX/LINUX security audits Experience working with DoD classified IT system security configuration and processes Working technical knowledge of UNIX/LINUX and Windows operating systems commands and utilities Excellent oral and written communication skills Experience in government IT security standards, policies and directives Proficiency in UNIX/LINUX audit analysis Proficiency in Windows log forwarding and audit analysis Help Desk experience Data Center experience Microsoft Office Application experience Ability to multi-task Experience conducting forensic analysis on audit log data for security incidents a plus Hands on Splunk application experience highly desired Applicants must meet DoD 8570.1 certification requirements for IAT-II or higher #CB #CJ3 Company Overview General Dynamics Mission Systems (GDMS) engineers a diverse portfolio of high technology solutions, products and services that enable customers to successfully execute missions across all domains of operation. With a global team of 12,000+ top professionals, we partner with the best in industry to expand the bounds of innovation in the defense and scientific arenas. Given the nature of our work and w